MIND diet and cognitive function and its decline: A prospective study and meta-analysis of prospective cohort studies.
Our findings suggest that higher adherence to the MIND diet was associated with better cognitive function and potentially slower cognitive decline in later life. Further large-scale observational and interventional studies are warranted to elucidate the cognitive effects of the MIND diet. Prospero registry number This meta-analysis was registered at PROSPERO as CRD42022330417.
