    A prospective study of waist circumference trajectories and incident cardiovascular disease in China: the Kailuan Cohort Study.
WC trajectory patterns were associated with altered risk of CVD among Chinese adults, even among people without BMI-defined obesity. When stratifying by age, the association was observed to be higher in younger adults. Am J Clin Nutr 2021; 113 338-347.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Association of development quotient with nutritional status of vitamins B6, B12, and folate in 6-59-month-old children: Results from the Brazilian National Survey on Child Nutrition (ENANI-2019).
In Brazil, the DQ is lower among older children, and those with vitamin B12 deficiency. Vitamin B6 status was directly associated with the DQ in children aged 24-59 months.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Associations of prenatal methylmercury exposure and maternal polyunsaturated fatty acid status with neurodevelopmental outcomes at 7 years of age: results from the Seychelles Child Development Study Nutrition Cohort 2.
Our findings do not support an association between prenatal MeHg exposure or maternal DHA and AA status with neurodevelopmental outcomes at age 7 y. The roles of n-6 and n-3 PUFA in child neurodevelopment need further research. Am J Clin Nutr 2021; 113 304-313.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
B-vitamin treatment modifies the mortality risk associated with calcium channel blockers in patients with suspected stable angina pectoris: A prospective cohort study.
In patients with suspected SAP, CCB treatment was associated with increased mortality risk primarily among patients not treated with B-vitamins. Clinical trial registration-url Clinical Trial Registration-Unique identifier (NCT number)  NCT00354081.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Best (but oft forgotten) statistical practices: Measuring real-world intervention effectiveness using electronic health data.
However, real-world intervention effectiveness studies using electronic health data face many challenges including data quality, selection bias, confounding by indication, and lack of generalizability. In this article, we describe the key barriers to generating high-quality evidence from real-world intervention effectiveness studies and suggest statistical best practices for addressing them.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Estimating the serum folate concentration that corresponds to the red blood cell folate concentration threshold associated with optimal neural tube defects prevention: A population-based biomarker survey in Southern India.
Objectives This study aimed to estimate the serum folate insufficiency threshold corresponding to the RBC folate threshold for NTD prevention and examine how this threshold is modified by vitamin B insufficiency. Am J Clin Nutr 2023; xx:xx-xx.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Fetal iron uptake from recent maternal diet and the maternal RBC iron pool.
Iron absorption doubled from T2 to T3 as maternal TBI declined. Women with low TBI had a greater decrease in RBC iron enrichment and transferred more RBC-derived iron to their neonate. These findings suggest maternal RBC iron serves as a significant source of iron for the fetus, particularly in women with depleted body iron stores. Am J Clin Nutr 2022; 115 1069-1079.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Healthful plant-based dietary pattern and risk of hepatocellular carcinoma in a multiethnic population: a cohort study.
Greater adherence to plant-based diets rich in healthy plant foods and low in less healthy plant foods is associated with a reduced risk of HCC in a multiethnic population.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Leisure-time and study-time Internet use and dietary risk factors in Korean adolescents.
Our data suggest that prolonged Internet use, particularly during leisure time, is associated with less healthful dietary behaviors in Korean adolescents. Am J Clin Nutr 2021; 114 1791-1801.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Metabolic signature of healthy lifestyle and risk of rheumatoid arthritis: observational and Mendelian randomization study.
 Our findings implicate the metabolic signature reflecting healthy lifestyle as a potential causal mediator in the development of RA, highlighting the importance of early lifestyle intervention and metabolic tracking for precise prevention of RA.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Probiotics for children with uncomplicated severe acute malnutrition (PruSAM study): A randomized controlled trial in the Democratic Republic of Congo.
This trial supports using probiotics for the treatment of children with uncomplicated SAM. Its effect on diarrhea could positively affect nutritional programs in resource-limited settings. This trial was registered as PACTR202108842939734.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Inflamm Bowel Dis
    Predicting Endoscopic Improvement in Ulcerative Colitis Using the Ulcerative Colitis Severity Index.
 The UCSI is an internally validated prognostic scoring tool that accurately predicts 1-year EI at baseline among moderate-to-severe UC patients initiating therapy. Further validation with additional datasets is needed.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
J Crohns Colitis
    Obefazimod: A First-in-class Drug for the Treatment of Ulcerative Colitis.
With a novel mechanism of action, obefazimod is an orally available small molecule with anti-inflammatory properties through the specific and selective upregulation of miR-124 expression. The aim of this paper is to critically review the available evidence related to pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics, and to discuss the potential clinical implications of this first-in-class oral small molecule.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Liver Transpl
    Reduced metabolic flexibility is a predictor of weight gain among liver transplant recipients. 
Inefficient transition between biofuels (carbohydrates and fatty acids) is associated with weight gain in LT recipients that is independent of clinical metabolic risk. These data offer novel insight into the physiology of obesity post-LT with potential to develop new diagnostics and therapeutics.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Pancreatology
    Machine learning versus regression for prediction of sporadic pancreatic cancer.
The three models complement each other, but each has unique contributions.
Pubmed   Journal   ReadQx 
Mortality and costs related to severe acute pancreatitis in the intensive care units of Australia and New Zealand (ANZ), 2003-2020.
In critically-ill SAP patients in ANZ, no change in mortality has been noted over nearly two decades. There was a slight reduction in hospital stay (1 day), while the length of ICU stay remained unchanged. Given the significant costs related to care of patients with SAP in ICU, these findings highlight the need to prioritise resource allocation for healthcare delivery and targeted clinical research to identify treatments aimed at reducing mortality.
